HEADWORD: Upbar
<hw>Up*bar"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
fasten with a bar.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To remove the bar or bards of, as a gate; to
under.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Upbear</ent>⟦br⟧
